<section>
    <div class="page-header">
        <h2 id="icons">Icons</h2>
    </div>

    <p>BraincraftedBootstrapBundle provides a function to include Glyphicons in templates.</p>

    <pre><code class="twig">{{ "&lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; class=&quot;btn btn-default btn-lg&quot;&gt;{{ icon('camera') }} Camera&lt;/button&gt;" }}</code></pre>

    <div class="panel">
        <div class="panel-body disable-links">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-lg">{{ icon('camera') }} Camera</button>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-footer">Button with icon</div>
    </div>

    <p>A filter to parse icons from a string of text is also provided. Just use <code>.icon-NAME</code> anywhere in the string and the filter will replace it with the HTML code.</p>

    <pre><code class="twig">{{ "{{ 'This is the story of a .icon-paperclip that travled the .icon-globe with his .icon-headphones on.'|parse_icons }}" }}</code></pre>

    <div class="panel">
        <div class="panel-body disable-links">
            {{ 'This is the story of a .icon-paperclip that travled the .icon-globe with his .icon-headphones on.'|parse_icons }}
        </div>
        <div class="panel-footer">Icons defined inside a string</div>
    </div>

    <p>{{ label_info('Info') }} You need to install the Glyphicon icon font before this will work. More information are in the <a href="{{ path('braincrafted_bootstrap_getting_started') }}#installing-glyphicons">installation instructions</a>.</p>


</section>